rance</a> from your vendor profile, or find them inside your portal account dashboard.</li><li>Sole-Source Verification: Formal <a href='/pages/vendor-profile'>sole-source letters</a> are available for products manufactured exclusively for our catalog to simplify non-competitive bids.</li><li>Invoice Compatibility: Our billing system allows for manual reconciliation to ensure final invoices line up with your district purchasing requirements.</li></ul></div></details><details><summary>Replacement Parts &amp; Care</summary><div class='body'><ul><li>Hardwood Care: Wipe with a damp cloth and mild soap. Do not submerge wood pieces in water, place them in a dishwasher, or use harsh chemical bleach sprays.</li><li>Pure Wool Felt: Spot clean gently with a damp cloth and cool water. Avoid scrubbing, machine washing, or using heat, as heat and friction will cause wool fibers to shrink and felt further.</li><li>Therapy Dough Longevity: Always store Análú dough in its air-tight tin immediately after play sessions. If left out overnight, knead a few drops of water back into the dough to fully restore its original pliability.</li><li>Eco Cutters: Hand wash your bio-plastic PLA cutters in cool, soapy water. Do not expose them to hot water, sanitizing machines, or dishwashers, as high temperatures will warp the plant-based material.</li><li>Component Support: Missing pieces happen in busy classrooms. Contact <a href='mailto:educators@mytoywagon.com'>educators@mytoywagon.com</a> for school-specific replacement component availability to restore your complete play sets.</li></ul></div></details></div>"
